---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Resources & Books">
  <article class="container page-section">
    <h1>Resources for Recovery</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 650px;">
      Books, online programs, practitioner directories, podcasts, videos, and scientific
      articles to support your understanding and recovery.
    </p>

    <h2>Essential Books</h2>

    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin: 1rem 0;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.25rem; font-size: 1rem;">The Way Out — Alan Gordon & Alon Ziv</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          The definitive guide to Pain Reprocessing Therapy. Written by its creator — clear, practical,
          and science-backed. Includes step-by-step instructions for somatic tracking and the full PRT
          protocol. Best starting point for most people.
          <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Way-Out-Revolutionary-Scientifically-Approach/dp/059308683X" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Amazon →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.25rem; font-size: 1rem;">Unlearn Your Pain — Howard Schubiner, MD</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          A workbook-format program with exercises, journal prompts, and guided activities for
          reversing neuroplastic pain. The 4th edition includes expanded emotional processing work.
          Also available: <em>Unlearn Your Anxiety & Depression</em> workbook.
          <a href="https://unlearnyourpain.com/unlearn-your-pain-book/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Order →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.25rem; font-size: 1rem;">Unlearn Your Pain (New Edition, 2026) — Howard Schubiner, MD</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          Published by Penguin/Random House. Covers the full spectrum: chronic pain, fatigue, anxiety,
          and depression — all addressed through the same neuroplastic framework.
          <a href="https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/782218/unlearn-your-pain-by-howard-schubiner-md-foreword-by-kate-murphy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Order →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.25rem; font-size: 1rem;">Healing Back Pain — John E. Sarno, MD</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          The original book that started the mind-body pain movement. While the neuroscience has
          advanced significantly since 1991, Sarno's clinical insights remain remarkably accurate.
          Quick read — most people finish it in a few hours.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.25rem; font-size: 1rem;">The Mindbody Prescription — John E. Sarno, MD</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          Sarno's deeper exploration of how repressed emotions create physical symptoms. Covers a
          wider range of conditions (not just back pain) and includes more detailed psychological analysis.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.25rem; font-size: 1rem;">Hidden From View — Allan Abbass, MD & Howard Schubiner, MD</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          A clinician's guide to understanding and treating mind-body conditions using ISTDP
          and related approaches. More technical but excellent for deeper understanding of
          the emotional-physical connection.
          <a href="https://unlearnyourpain.com/hidden-from-view-book/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Order →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--teal);">
        <h3 style="margin: 0 0 0.25rem; font-size: 1rem;">Explain Pain — David Butler & Lorimer Moseley</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          The classic pain science text used by clinicians worldwide. Dense with illustrations and
          metaphors that make complex neuroscience accessible. Excellent supplement to the treatment
          books above.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Online Programs & Courses</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin: 1rem 0;">
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Freedom From Chronic Pain</strong> — Schubiner's comprehensive online mind-body program.
        <a href="https://www.freedomfromchronicpain.com/#enrol" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Coursera: Reign of Pain</strong> — Low-cost course by Schubiner on the neuroplastic pain paradigm.
        <a href="https://www.coursera.org/learn/reign-of-pain" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>PRT Healing Workshops</strong> — 8-week virtual group program with expert PRT recovery coaches.
        <a href="https://www.painreprocessingtherapy.com/healing-workshop" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>WellBody Psychotherapy</strong> — One-on-one PRT sessions with trained providers.
        <a href="https://getwellbody.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Ovid Dx</strong> — Mobile training course for learning about and treating mind-body conditions.
        <a href="https://oviddx.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Beyond Pain Education</strong> — Course for understanding and treating neuroplastic pain.
        <a href="https://www.mperformance.com/product-page/beyond-pain-education" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Apps</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin: 1rem 0;">
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Curable</strong> — Guided program combining pain science education, meditation, and somatic tracking exercises. Built on PRT and PNE principles. Evidence-informed.
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Unlearn Your Pain App</strong> — Companion app with Schubiner's meditations, tracking tools, and daily exercises.
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Waking Up</strong> — Meditation app by Sam Harris with pain-focused content, including discussions with pain researchers.
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Find a Practitioner</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin: 1rem 0;">
      <div class="card">
        <strong>PRT Practitioner Directory</strong> — Search for PRT-trained physicians, therapists, coaches, and manual therapists.
        <a href="https://www.painreprocessingtherapy.com/directory-of-practitioners" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Browse →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>ATNS Practitioner Directory</strong> — Directory of practitioners trained in neuroplastic symptom treatment.
        <a href="https://www.symptomatic.me/practitioner-directory" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Browse →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Cormendi Health</strong> — Telehealth practice where Dr. Schubiner sees patients (2-visit model: initial assessment + follow-up).
        <a href="https://cormendihealth.com/contact-us-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Psychology Today</strong> — Therapist finder — filter by "Chronic Pain" and ask potential therapists about their familiarity with PRT, EAET, or mind-body approaches.
        <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/therapists" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Browse →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Podcasts</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin: 1rem 0;">
      {[
        { title: 'The Science Behind the Symptoms', host: 'Howard Schubiner, MD & Becca Kennedy, MD', url: 'https://www.symptomatic.me/thesciencebehindthesymptoms' },
        { title: 'The Story Behind the Symptoms', host: 'David Clarke, MD', url: 'https://www.symptomatic.me/thestorybehindthesymptoms' },
        { title: 'The Cure for Chronic Pain', host: 'Nicole Sachs, LCSW', url: 'https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/the-cure-for-chronic-pain-with-nicole-sachs-lcsw/id1439580309' },
        { title: 'Tell Me About Your Pain', host: 'Alan Gordon & Alon Ziv', url: 'https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/tell-me-about-your-pain/id1503847664' },
        { title: 'Curable Podcast (Like Mind, Like Body)', host: 'Curable team', url: 'https://www.curablehealth.com/podcast' },
        { title: 'Crushing Doubt', host: 'Dan Ratner', url: 'https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/crushing-doubt-with-dr-dan-ratner/id1538668164' },
      ].map(p => (
        <div class="card" style="padding: 0.9rem 1rem;">
          <strong>{p.title}</strong>
          <p style="margin: 0.1rem 0 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted);">{p.host}</p>
          <a href={p.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">Listen →</a>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h2>Videos & Documentaries</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin: 1rem 0;">
      <div class="card">
        <strong>This Might Hurt</strong> — Documentary film following chronic pain patients through mind-body treatment. Features Schubiner and others.
        <a href="https://www.thismighthurtfilm.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Watch →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Schubiner's Animated Mind-Body Series</strong> — 6 short videos explaining predictive processing and neuroplastic pain clearly.
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLsJVYZbo6uWrKc57MDUL1vGciEGnPYrV9" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Watch →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>The Reign of Pain</strong> — Schubiner's 22-minute overview of the new pain paradigm.
        <a href="https://unlearnyourpain.com/mind-body-videos/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Watch →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Talks at Google</strong> — Schubiner's presentation on breakthrough healing for chronic pain.
        <a href="https://unlearnyourpain.com/mind-body-videos/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Watch →</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Lorimer Moseley's TED Talk & Explainer Videos</strong> — Search YouTube for "Tame the Beast" and "Why Things Hurt." Excellent pain science animations.
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Key Scientific Papers</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin: 1rem 0;">
      {[
        { title: 'Effect of Pain Reprocessing Therapy vs Placebo and Usual Care for Patients With Chronic Back Pain', journal: 'JAMA Psychiatry (2021)', note: 'The Boulder PRT study — 66% pain-free, 98% improved', url: 'https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamapsychiatry/fullarticle/2784694' },
        { title: 'Five-Year Follow-up of Pain Reprocessing Therapy', journal: 'JAMA Psychiatry (2024)', note: 'Long-term follow-up confirming persistent results', url: 'https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamapsychiatry/article-abstract/2837160' },
        { title: 'PRT Mechanism: Pain Reattribution from Body to Brain', journal: 'JAMA Network Open (2023)', note: 'Secondary analysis showing how PRT works', url: 'https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamanetworkopen/fullarticle/2809959' },
        { title: 'EAET vs CBT for Fibromyalgia', journal: 'PAIN (2017)', note: 'Emotional processing outperforms cognitive approach', url: 'https://journals.lww.com/pain/Abstract/2017/12000/Emotional_awareness_and_expression_therapy,.10.aspx' },
        { title: 'EAET for Older Veterans with Chronic Pain', journal: 'Pain Medicine (2020)', note: 'EAET superior to CBT in veteran population', url: 'https://unlearnyourpain.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Yarns-et-al.-2020.-EAET-achieves-greater-pain-reduction-than-CBT-in-older-adults-with-pain.-RCT.pdf' },
        { title: 'Psychological Therapy for Centralized Pain (Review)', journal: 'Psychosomatic Medicine (2019)', note: 'Integrative assessment and treatment model by Lumley & Schubiner', url: 'https://unlearnyourpain.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Lumley-Schubiner-2019.-Psychological-therapy-for-centralized-pain.-Integrative-assessment-and-treatment-model-1.pdf' },
        { title: 'Harvard PSRT Pilot RCT', journal: 'JAMA Network Open (2021)', note: 'Psychophysiologic Symptom Relief Therapy shows significant results', url: 'https://unlearnyourpain.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Donnino-et-al.-2021.-Psychophysiologic-symptom-relief-therapy-for-chronoic-back-pain.-Pilot-RCT.pdf' },
        { title: 'Prevalence of Primary (Neuroplastic) Back & Neck Pain', journal: 'Journal of Pain (2024)', note: 'Vast majority lack structural cause', url: 'https://unlearnyourpain.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Schubiner-et-al2023-Application-of-a-clinical-approach-to-diagnosing-primary-pain.pdf' },
        { title: 'Racism as a Source of Pain', journal: 'Journal of General Internal Medicine (2023)', note: 'Racial discrimination generates neuroplastic symptoms', url: 'https://unlearnyourpain.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Racism-as-a-source-of-pain-pdf.pdf' },
      ].map(p => (
        <div class="card" style="padding: 0.9rem 1rem;">
          <strong style="font-size: 0.95rem;">{p.title}</strong>
          <p style="margin: 0.15rem 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted);">{p.journal} — {p.note}</p>
          <a href={p.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">Read →</a>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="background: var(--teal-light); margin-top: 2rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Resources listed are educational suggestions, not medical endorsements.
        Always research any practitioner or program before committing. Results vary. This site has
        no financial relationship with any of the resources listed above.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
